  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Charcoal Black sits in the heart of the gray spectrum for Landmark. It reads as a clean charcoal in direct sun and softens to a near-black on cloudy or shaded elevations. That tonal range is the reason it dominates the dimensional asphalt category nationally.",
      "Up close you can pick out three or four granule shades layered into the surface. From the street they collapse into one mid-dark gray, but the layering is why a quality asphalt roof catches light the way single-color metal never quite does.",
      "Difficult to pair badly. The one place it disagrees: bright primary-yellow houses, where the cool undertone fights the warm siding."
    ],
